2\. TypeScript Props and State Interfaces

These interfaces define the contract between the Workspace Composition
Engine (which determines which components to render and with what
parameters) and the React components (which render the data). All
monetary values are numbers in dollars (not cents). All dates are ISO
8601 strings. Service years are decimal numbers (e.g., 28.75).

> **CROSS-STREAM:** S3 (API) must produce response schemas that directly
> map to these interfaces. The Intelligence Service response for each
> endpoint should be directly assignable to the corresponding component
> props without transformation layers. Any mismatch between API response
> shape and these interfaces must be flagged for resolution.

MemberBanner

> // === MemberBanner ===
>
> interface MemberBannerProps {
>
> member: MemberIdentity;
>
> compact?: boolean; // collapsed for constrained layouts
>
> onExpandToggle?: () =\> void;
>
> }
>
> interface MemberIdentity {
>
> memberId: string;
>
> firstName: string;
>
> lastName: string;
>
> dateOfBirth: string; // ISO 8601
>
> ageAtDate: number; // computed for context date
>
> tier: 1 \| 2 \| 3;
>
> tierLabel: string; // \'Pre-2004\' \| \'Sept 2004-June 2011\' \|
> \'Post-July 2011\'
>
> status: MemberStatus;
>
> department: string;
>
> position: string;
>
> hireDate: string;
>
> totalServiceYears: number;
>
> totalServiceMonths: number;
>
> earnedServiceYears: number;
>
> purchasedServiceYears: number;
>
> ssnLast4?: string; // masked display only
>
> maritalStatus?: \'single\' \| \'married\' \| \'divorced\' \|
> \'widowed\';
>
> hasDRO: boolean;
>
> hasDataQualityIssues: boolean;
>
> }
>
> type MemberStatus = \'active\' \| \'inactive\' \| \'retired\' \|
> \'deceased\' \| \'refunded\';

AlertBar

> // === AlertBar ===
>
