Shared Types

> // === Shared Types (used across components) ===
>
> type InteractionType = \'static\' \| \'drillable\' \| \'explainable\';
>
> interface DataQualityFlag {
>
> id: string;
>
> severity: \'critical\' \| \'high\' \| \'medium\' \| \'low\';
>
> message: string;
>
> field: string;
>
> proposedCorrection?: string;
>
> }
>
> // Workspace Composition Types
>
> interface WorkspaceDefinition {
>
> memberId: string;
>
> processType: \'service_retirement\';
>
> processStage: ProcessStage;
>
> compositionTier: 1 \| 2 \| 3; // highest tier used
>
> components: ComponentSlot\[\];
>
> degradationLevel: 0 \| 1 \| 2 \| 3 \| 4 \| 5; // per ADR-007
>
> composedAt: string;
>
> }
>
> interface ComponentSlot {
>
> componentId: string; // e.g., \'benefit-calculation-panel\'
>
> initialState: \'expanded\' \| \'collapsed\' \| \'summary\';
>
> order: number; // display ordering
>
> contextParams: Record\<string, unknown\>; // tier-specific config
>
> compositionTier: 1 \| 2; // which tier added this
>
> required: boolean; // false = can be removed by user
>
> }
>
> type ProcessStage =
>
> \| \'application_review\'
>
> \| \'employment_verification\'
>
> \| \'salary_verification\'
>
> \| \'eligibility_determination\'
>
> \| \'benefit_calculation\'
>
> \| \'payment_option_selection\'
>
> \| \'final_certification\';

3\. Workspace Composition Decision Tree

The composition engine receives three inputs: member context (identity,
tier, status, flags), process context (type, current stage), and
situational context (DRO present, purchased service, leave payout
eligible, threshold proximity). It produces a WorkspaceDefinition
containing the ordered list of components with their initial states and
configuration parameters.

Critical principle from architecture: \'Show everything, prioritize what
matters.\' Default to inclusion, not exclusion. Tier 2 rules ADD
components for relevance; they rarely REMOVE. The result is a workspace
where the worker sees the full picture with situational components
promoted to prominence.

3.1 Tier 1 (Deterministic): Base Workspace for Service Retirement

Every service retirement case, regardless of tier or situation, receives
these components. Tier 1 composition uses process configuration only and
executes in sub-100ms.

  ------------------------------ --------------- --------------- -------------- ------------
  **Component**                  **Initial       **Order**       **Required**   **Source**
                                 State**                                        

  **MemberBanner**               expanded        1 (always       Yes            Process
                                                 first)                         config

  **AlertBar**                   expanded        2 (below        Yes            Process
                                                 banner)                        config

  **EmploymentTimeline**         collapsed       3               Yes            Process
                                                                                config

  **SalaryTable**                collapsed       4               Yes            Process
                                                                                config

  **BenefitCalculationPanel**    expanded        5 (centerpiece) Yes            Process
                                                                                config

  **PaymentOptionsComparison**   collapsed       6               Yes            Process
                                                                                config

  **IPRCalculator**              collapsed       7               Yes            Process
                                                                                config
  ------------------------------ --------------- --------------- -------------- ------------

3.2 Tier 2 (Rule-Based): Situational Component Addition

Tier 2 evaluates member context (tier, flags, eligibility path) and
conditionally adds, removes, or reconfigures components. Executes in
sub-100ms via deterministic conditional logic. No AI involved.

  ------------------------------------------------- -------------------------------------------------- ------------------------------------- --------------
  **Condition**                                     **Action**                                         **Component(s)**                      **Demo Case**

