                                                    (order 3.5, collapsed). No warning.                                                      

  **leavePayout.eligible === true**                 ADD LeavePayoutCalculator adjacent to SalaryTable  LeavePayoutCalculator, AlertBar       Case 1 (Case
                                                    (order 4.5). ADD alert (info): \'Leave payout      update                                4)
                                                    eligible --- impacts AMS calculation\'. SET                                              
                                                    SalaryTable to highlight payout month.                                                   

  **leavePayout.eligible === false**                No LeavePayoutCalculator. No payout alert.         (none)                                Cases 2, 3

  **member.maritalStatus === \'married\'**          ADD alert (warning): \'Spousal consent required    AlertBar update                       Cases 1, 4
                                                    for payment option selection (RMC §18-403(d))\'.                                         
                                                    Minimum 50% J&S unless spouse waives.                                                    

  **scenarioModeler.thresholdProximity.pointsAway   ADD ScenarioModeler in expanded state after        ScenarioModeler, AlertBar update      Case 2
  \<= 5**                                           BenefitCalculationPanel (order 5.7). ADD alert                                           
                                                    (info): \'Member is X points from Rule of 75/85                                          
                                                    --- scenario comparison available\'.                                                     

  **eligibility.type === \'normal\' (age 65+)**     No reduction calculator. No scenario modeler       (none)                                (no demo case)
                                                    (already at normal retirement).                                                          
  ------------------------------------------------- -------------------------------------------------- ------------------------------------- --------------

