3.4 Tier 3 (AI Augmentation): Edge Cases

Tier 3 composition is invoked only for genuinely novel situations not
covered by Tier 1+2 rules. For the POC, Tier 3 is not exercised by any
of the four demo cases. The composition engine logs when it would have
invoked Tier 3, enabling post-deployment analysis of edge case
frequency.

Per ADR-007, the workspace is fully functional without AI service. If AI
is unavailable, the system falls back to Tier 1+2 composition (which
handles all four demo cases) and logs the fallback event.

> **CROSS-STREAM:** S3 (API) must ensure the /api/v1/workspace/compose
> endpoint returns a WorkspaceDefinition matching this decision tree.
> The endpoint receives member context + process context and returns the
> component list with ordering and state. S3 must define the
> CompositionRequest and CompositionResponse schemas.
>
> **CROSS-STREAM:** S2 (Rules) must expose eligibility determination
> results (type, reduction, threshold proximity) in the response from
> /api/v1/eligibility/evaluate so that Tier 2 composition rules can
> consume them without re-computing.

4\. Accessibility Requirements (Section 508 Compliance)

All components must meet Section 508 compliance (per 36 CFR Part 1194)
and WCAG 2.1 Level AA. This is non-negotiable for government-facing
software. The following requirements apply universally, followed by
component-specific requirements.

4.1 Universal Requirements

  ------------------ ----------------------------------------------------
  **Requirement**    **Implementation**

  **Color contrast** All text/background combinations meet WCAG AA: 4.5:1
                     for normal text (\< 18pt), 3:1 for large text (18pt+
                     or 14pt bold). Design system tokens are
                     pre-validated. Tier badge colors validated: Tier 1
                     blue #3B82F6 on #EBF5FF (5.2:1), Tier 2 amber
                     #B45309 on #FFF3E0 (4.8:1), Tier 3 green #15803D on
                     #E8F5E9 (5.1:1).

  **Keyboard         All interactive elements reachable via Tab. Logical
  navigation**       tab order follows visual order (component ordering
                     from composition). No keyboard traps.
                     Skip-to-content link at page top. Escape key closes
                     modals/popovers and returns focus to trigger.

  **Focus            Visible focus ring: 2px solid
  indicators**       var(\--noui-border-focus) with 2px offset. Never
                     removed (no outline: none). Focus visible on all
                     interactive elements including drill-down triggers,
                     radio buttons, sort headers, and dismiss buttons.

  **Screen reader    Semantic HTML elements (\<header\>, \<main\>,
  support**          \<nav\>, \<table\>, \<section\>). ARIA landmarks for
                     workspace zones. aria-live regions for dynamic
                     content updates (alert dismissals, calculation
                     results, scenario comparisons). aria-describedby for
                     fields with statutory references.

  **Color not sole   Status conveyed by icon + color + text label (never
  indicator**        color alone). Tier identification includes text
                     label (\'Tier 1\') alongside badge color. AMS window
                     rows use background color AND a marker icon/text
                     prefix. Data quality severity uses icon + color +
                     label.

  **Text resizing**  All text renders correctly at 200% zoom. No content
                     clipping or overlap. Components reflow to single
                     column at reduced viewport. Monospace values
                     maintain alignment at larger sizes.

  **Motion and       All animations respect prefers-reduced-motion media
  animation**        query. When reduced motion preferred: no staggered
                     component entry, no expand/collapse transitions, no
                     progress bar animations. Functional behavior
                     unchanged.

  **Error            Form validation errors identified by: red border on
  identification**   field, error icon adjacent to field, descriptive
                     error text below field linked via aria-describedby,
                     and focus moved to first error on submission.
  ------------------ ----------------------------------------------------

