4.3 Testing Requirements

Accessibility testing is integrated into the build process, not added as
an afterthought. The following testing matrix applies:

  --------------- ------------------------- ---------------------------------
  **Test Type**   **Tool**                  **Scope**

  **Automated     axe-core (via             Every component rendered in
  scanning**      \@axe-core/react or       isolation. Run on every PR. Zero
                  vitest-axe)               violations at \'critical\' and
                                            \'serious\' severity.

  **Keyboard      Manual (documented script Tab order, focus visibility,
  testing**       per component)            keyboard activation, escape
                                            behavior, no traps. One pass per
                                            component per build day.

  **Screen reader VoiceOver (macOS) or NVDA Full workspace composition for
  testing**       (Windows)                 each demo case. All four cases
                                            tested before POC demo. Verify
                                            announcements match expected
                                            content.

  **Color         Colour Contrast Analyser  All design system token pairs
  contrast        or axe                    verified. Any custom or dynamic
  audit**                                   colors checked at component
                                            level.

  **Reduced       prefers-reduced-motion:   All animations disabled. No
  motion**        reduce in dev tools       functional loss. Visual layout
                                            unchanged.
  --------------- ------------------------- ---------------------------------

> **CROSS-STREAM:** S5 (Test) must include accessibility test stubs in
> the verification framework. Each component test file should include an
> axe-core render test. The four demo case acceptance tests must include
> a keyboard-only walkthrough scenario.

5\. Cross-Stream Discovery Summary

The following discoveries during S4 analysis affect other parallel
design streams:

5.1 Discoveries for S1 (Database/Data Model)

> **CROSS-STREAM:** The LeavePayoutCalculator requires leave balance
> data (sick hours, vacation hours, hourly rate) not explicitly called
> out in the current entity list. S1 must confirm whether this comes
> from the legacy database or is a derived field in the data connector.
>
> **CROSS-STREAM:** The ScenarioModeler requires the ability to project
> future salary and service for hypothetical retirement dates. S1 must
> define whether this projection logic lives in the data connector or
> the intelligence service.

5.2 Discoveries for S2 (Business Rules)

> **CROSS-STREAM:** The lump-sum death benefit calculation differs by
> tier and eligibility type (normal vs. early retirement). Tiers 1/2
> reduce by \$250/year under 65; Tier 3 reduces by \$500/year under 65.
> S2 must ensure this is included in the benefit calculation rule set.
> The PaymentOptionsComparison component needs this value.
>
> **CROSS-STREAM:** The composition decision tree relies on a
> \'threshold proximity\' score (points away from Rule of 75/85). S2
> must expose this as part of the eligibility evaluation response, not
> just the binary met/not-met. Specifically: { pointsAway: number,
> dateThresholdMet: string }.

5.3 Discoveries for S3 (API)

> **CROSS-STREAM:** The workspace composition endpoint must return
> component ordering as fractional numbers (e.g., 5.3, 5.5, 5.7) to
> support Tier 2 insertion between Tier 1 base components. The
> ComponentSlot.order field must be a float, not an integer.
>
> **CROSS-STREAM:** The BenefitCalculationPanel requires an
> \'explainable\' field metadata layer. Each numeric value in the
> calculation response should include an interactionType field
> indicating whether it can be drilled down or explained. This extends
> the standard API response pattern and must be documented in the
> OpenAPI spec.

5.4 Discoveries for S5 (Test/Verification)

> **CROSS-STREAM:** Each demo case must have a corresponding \'expected
> workspace composition\' test fixture specifying the exact component
> list, ordering, and initial states. These fixtures validate the
> composition engine independently from the calculation engine.
>
> **CROSS-STREAM:** Accessibility acceptance tests must cover all four
> demo cases with keyboard-only navigation. The test should verify that
> every component in the composed workspace is reachable and operable
> without a mouse.

